---
import SiteLayout from '../components/SiteLayout.astro';
import { ROUTES } from '../lib/ia';

const requestedPath = Astro.url.pathname;
---

<SiteLayout
  title="Page Not Found"
  description="The requested Judgment Kit page could not be found."
  path="/404"
  robots="noindex,nofollow"
  bodyClass="not-found-page"
>
  <section aria-labelledby="not-found-title" class="platform-hero">
    <div class="hero-copy">
      <span class="eyebrow">404</span>
      <h1 id="not-found-title">That page does not exist.</h1>
      <p class="subhead">
        The route <code>{requestedPath}</code> is not part of the current JudgmentKit public
        library.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you followed an old link or typed a path manually, use the kits library or the resource
        library to jump back into the published information architecture.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a class="button primary" href={ROUTES.kits}>Browse kits</a>
        <a class="button ghost" href={ROUTES.resources}>Browse resources</a>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-sidebar">
      <article class="summary-card">
        <strong>Canonical routes</strong>
        <p>`/` for the platform, `/kits` for operating kits, and `/resources` for the full public library.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="summary-card">
        <strong>Need review-only layouts?</strong>
        <p>The internal exploration routes still live under <a href="/review">`/review`</a> and are intentionally non-canonical.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="summary-card">
        <strong>Most likely next step</strong>
        <p>Read the Design Judgment Kit, then use `/resources` when you need workflow-governance detail.</p>
        <a href={ROUTES.designKit}>Read Design Judgment Kit</a>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</SiteLayout>
